structured.title: Friends Discuss Football Management Mobile Game
structured.overview: The user and a friend chat informally about a football management-style mobile game (accessed via Netflix), where the player acts as the club chairman rather than the manager. They mention divisions (Division 1 and 2), rating systems, a 65-rated attacker, promotion history from non-league in 2026 up to League Two, and features like stadium expansion and adding food options. The rest of the dialogue is casual side comments about the tight space and recording device.

## Game and Platform Details

## Team and Player Status
- Best attacker rated 65 overall  
- Currently in Division 1 or Division 2  
- Different rating system than other football games  

## Club Progression and History
- Start year: 2026 in non-league C  
- Spent 3-4 seasons in non-league C  
- Then about 1 hour in League Two  

## Gameplay Mechanics and Role
- Player acts as chairman, not manager  
- Must expand and upgrade stadium size  
- Can add facilities like food services  

## Next Steps
- Continue climbing from Division 2 upwards  
- Further upgrade stadium and club facilities
